<%= render "shared/header" %>

<div class="noise"></div>
<div class="cursor-glow" id="glow"></div>

<main>
  <section class="section internal-hero">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">Assistance</div>
      <h1>Common <span class="gold">questions</span> about the lab.</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 26px">Everything you need to know about our process, pricing, and project timelines.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list reveal">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is your typical project timeline?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most immersive websites take 4-8 weeks from discovery to launch. SaaS dashboards and complex systems typically range from 8-16 weeks depending on scope.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do you price your services?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">We work on a project-based pricing model for defined scopes, and a monthly retainer model for ongoing server management and infrastructure support.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you handle hosting and maintenance?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. We specialize in VPS setups, SSL management, automated backups, and 24/7 monitoring so you never have to worry about downtime.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you help with an existing codebase?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">We prefer starting from scratch to ensure the highest quality standards, but we do offer architectural reviews and optimization sprints for existing Rails/Node.js products.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block reveal">
      <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 20px">Our team is happy to jump on a quick call to discuss your specific needs.</p>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="mailto:hello@vanillalabs.io" class="btn primary">Contact support</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<%= render "shared/footer" %>
